The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | GAIL profit plunges 30%
                                                                                                               GAIL profit plunges 30%
          OUR BUREAU                                            
	Oct. 28: State-run gas transporter GAIL (India) Ltd today reported a 30 per cent decline in net profit at Rs 713.23 crore for the second-quarter ended September because of falling margins in petrochemicals and liquid hydrocarbons.        
	Net profit stood at Rs 1,023.45 crore during the year-ago period.        
	Half-yearly net profit dropped 29.1 per cent to Rs 13,690 crore from Rs 19,200 crore in 2008-09.        
	Prices of petrochemicals have fluctuated 10 per cent year-on-year while those of liquid hydrocarbons fell 40 per cent, chairman and managing director B.C. Tripathy said.        
	The GAIL board, which approved the results, has also decided to raise Rs 500 crore through a bond issue in early December.         
	Our board has approved raising of funds from the market and we will issue bonds for Rs 500 crore with a greenshoe option of 50 per cent, Tripathi said.        
	Total income during the second quarter rose 0.3 per cent to Rs 6,370 crore from Rs 6,350 crore a year ago.        
	Tata Tea net        
	Tata Tea has posted a net profit of Rs 258.04 crore in the July-September quarter on a standalone basis against Rs 43.79 crore in the year-ago period.        
	Consolidated net profit rose to Rs 287.44 crore from Rs 217.76 crore a year earlier.        
	Total operating income on a standalone basis grew to Rs 426.36 crore from Rs 324.32 crore a year ago.         
	Consolidated total income was up at Rs 1,402.82 crore against Rs 1,187.07 crore.        
	Eveready show        
	Eveready Industries net profit is up at Rs 17.54 crore for the quarter-ended September from Rs 2.26 crore a year ago.         
	Net sales grew 20 per cent to Rs 263 crore from Rs 220 crore a year ago.         
	The companys battery volumes grew 7 per cent during the quarter.        
	Evereadys packet tea business continued to leverage the companys battery distribution channel to push sales.                                                                                                                                        
